The relative usefulness of internal opinion polls.
Will internal opinion polls – like the questionnaire submitted to Orange employees – contribute to a revolution in management practices?
Unfortunately, I'm afraid not.
Mainly because I have already convinced myself that in the face of a new situation, the structure will return to what it has always done after different turns!
Furthermore, authoritarianism, as one of the pathologies of power, increases in proportion to the severity of one’s own failures.
Finally, because most managers have a simplified view of human behavior.
Because they are college graduates for engineers, they have a mechanical interpretation of psychology.
For the sake of thought convenience, they adopt an old behaviorist theory, currently revived by "neurosciences" from the United States and widely spread without much knowledge by scientific institutes and the media.
With the possibility of moving the "hebels" (sic) of the involvement of managers, a recent survey by the Ipsos agency showed on Figaro.fr, which only confirms the managers in their position of mechanical control, unsuitable for today's world.
Identify and measure mobilization factors.
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises presupposes the adoption of a final vision of human behavior.
It consists in integrating a fundamental insight into all management plans and practices: Commitments to the company will only be possible for employees if they appear to be a clear means of achieving their dreams, ambitions and projects.
