About one percent of people get schizophrenia at least once in their lives, in psychiatric clinics it is the second most commonly treated disease after depression.
In acute schizophrenic psychosis, the disabled can no longer distinguish between the inner and outer worlds, they get into an awakened state, which can lead to hallucinations, size, relationship illusions or the illusion of persecution.
Particularly widespread is the hearing of voices - voices that command, comment or conduct dialogues.
Even optical hallucinations are not uncommon.
The affected person is not able to distinguish the important from the unimportant, the brain cannot filter out disturbing signals, consciousness is flooded with impressions.
Like a dream, psychosis opens the door to a flood of thoughts and fantasies that come from the deepest layers of consciousness.
The perception of reality in psychosis is focused on the subject, says Professor Thomas Fuchs, chief physician of the General Psychiatry Clinic of the University Clinic in Heidelberg.
Schizophrenic is located in the center of events, everything has a meaning directed at it.
At the same time, he gets into a passive role, becomes, like in a dream, overwhelmed by events and cannot actively form them.
